14/12/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On the second day of the BiH Police Restructuring Commission's four-day session in Sarajevo Monday (13 December), BiH Security Minister Barisa Colak expressed optimism that the panel would agree on a concept for the future police structure in BiH, though he did not elaborate. 
Republika Srpska (RS) authorities have rejected the possible abolition of the RS police. 
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 14/12/04; PBS BiH, RTRS, Fena - 13/12/04)
